# Git-Worktree Skill References

This directory is reserved for additional reference documentation for the GIT-WORKTREE skill.

## Existing Documentation

The git-worktree skill maintains its existing documentation structure in the parent directory:

- `../README.md` - Comprehensive usage documentation and capabilities overview
- `../examples.md` - Detailed usage examples and common workflow scenarios  
- `../git-worktree.sh` - Main executable script with all worktree management functionality

## Backward Compatibility

All existing files and functionality have been preserved to maintain backward compatibility:
- Script functionality remains unchanged
- Documentation structure is maintained
- File paths and references are preserved
- Cross-platform compatibility is maintained

## Integration

The SKILL.md file references the existing documentation and scripts to provide Agent Skills compliance while preserving all existing functionality and file organization.
